description:
In this episode, Master Shi Heng Yi, Headmaster of Shaolin Temple Europe and author of Shaolin Spirit, reveals ancient Shaolin wisdom to help you find clarity, purpose, and peace in the chaos of modern life.

From breaking bricks with pure focus to breaking emotional patterns that keep us stuck, Master Shi shares the real reason we sufferand how to free yourself from anxiety, overthinking, addiction to achievement, and feeling never enough.

He explains:
- Why young men are struggling more than ever
- How to find your true purpose (without chasing external goals)
- The 5 internal forces holding every human back
- Why discipline and awarenessnot strengthlead to transformation
- How to reconnect with your inner power, even in a distracted world
- This isnt just an interview. Its a blueprint for spiritual, emotional, and mental mastery.

comments.text:
Thank. You both for a beautiful sharing.
   You both generated the energy of respectful patience.  
     A huge transformation in my life occurred in my Mid Twenties, my body stood up in a crowded room and it seemed like I was observing my body from about one foot above and behind my head.
    My voice started repeating the same words over and over for a few minutes and the feeling was incredible,  clear, ecstatic and an openness where I felt my mind/awareness expanding from first feeling the mind and thoughts of the 7 people in the room, shortly after I had the same experience but with a much larger circumference each time ... town absorbed, county absorbed,  all of Britain brought into the sharing and eventually I was looking down on the Earth and my awareness included not just the inhabitants but the actual planet was an alive ,feeling mind.
    The words that came...
  WE ARE ONE 
   WE ARE ALL ONE 
    WE ARE ONE 
     WE ARE ALL ONE...etc etc etc etc etc 
 This few minutes was without any mind altering substances and changed my life which was about 40 years ago. Several times I have nearly died and the last time was being ignored by my doctor for two and a half years which made the TUMOUR too large for surgery. 
    I sold everything I had of value including my beloved Motorbike for extra Cancer Treatments which saved my life. 
   I have been registered as Severely Disabled since then and I've been offered the choice of many brand new cars with full insurance including breakdown cover but I don't have a car licence,  I can only ride a motorbike but the government mobility scheme does nothing for motorcyclists which is discrimination against disabled motorcyclists. 
   I have tried saving for another bike but it is difficult to save on benefits. 
   Ideally I need someone to loan me around two thousand pounds and I could get a decent used bike and insure it. 
    I  can pay back 500 every 4 weeks and I will be more than happy to pay back extra. Because I am on benefits I can't get credit and I don't own my home. I had 4 jobs at the same time before I got ill and I had plenty of money and I was going to buy my Mother's house for her but I never reckoned upon becoming ill as I rode my ordinary bicycle a lot. I did Yoga, meditation and as a Reggae Dj I danced 5 hours per night so I felt fitter and fitter and I was totally surprised to get Cancer which I laughed  and joked all through the years with Cancer and when I was given the all clear, I went into a  bit of depression.  
   WOW I HAD EXACTLY THE SAME EXPERIENCE WHEN MY GRANDFATHER WAS DYING AND I GOT TIME ALONE JUST AS HE WAS PASSING AWAY AND HE SAID " DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT ME OUR PAUL, I AM FINE AND IN THAT MOMENT I LEARNED THAT THE GRIEF ALL THE FAMILY AND MY MOTHER WERE FEELING WAS SELFISH BECAUSE THEY WOULD MISS HIM. IT WASN'T FOR HIM. 
   Big Love to both of You 
  Namast
    Paul
